{"pageProps":{"news":{"_id":"605e2e1c14f2894457a29bda","title":"【超实用】2018 LSU Law Center退税指南","author":"宣传部","digest":"不懂保税退税？找LSU Law Center’s Tax Law Society 帮到你！","content":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><em>新的一年保税退税又开始啦，</em></span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><em>为了帮助国际学生和国际教职工，</em></span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><em>LSU Law Center’s Tax Law Society 会给大家提供有效的帮助。</em></span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br  /></span></em></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"\" data-backh=\"380\" data-backw=\"558\" data-copyright=\"0\" data-ratio=\"0.6818181818181818\" data-s=\"300,640\" data-src=\"https://mmbiz.qpic.cn/mmbiz_jpg/cGcYqtanUys41PbKrYtVPia4vaKDicUhyOvznib7Q6LvAwVOEwbe7n4DA74LESOwg6eUGud3wmdIgZAyuBCZG0iccg/640?wx_fmt=jpeg\" data-type=\"jpeg\" data-w=\"660\" style=\"width: 100%;height: auto;\"  /></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong><br  /></strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;background-color: rgb(255, 251, 0);\"><strong>✨重点✨</strong></span></p><p><br  /></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">时间</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">：</span><span style=\"font-size: 14px;text-decoration: none;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">2月20, 22, 27日；</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;text-decoration: none;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">3月1, 6, 7 &amp; 8 日；</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;text-decoration: none;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">下午6 - 8</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br  /></span></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">地点</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">：</span><span style=\"font-size: 14px;text-decoration: underline;\">Paul M. Hebert Law Center, Room W220 (side facing the Parade Grounds)&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br  /></span></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">携带文件</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">：</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"></span></p><ol class=\" list-paddingleft-2\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\"><li><p class=\"p1\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Passport, visa stamp and I-94&nbsp;</span><br  /></p></li><li><p class=\"p3\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"> Social Security Number (SSN) or Individual Taxpayer Identification Number (ITIN)&nbsp;</span></p></li><li><p class=\"p3\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">All tax forms received such as W-2, 1042-S, 1098-T, 1099-MISC, 1099-G, and 1099-R if applicable&nbsp;</span></p></li><li><p class=\"p2\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Proof of bank account routing numbers and account numbers (i.e. blank check), if you wish to use direct deposit&nbsp;</span></p></li><li><p class=\"p3\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"> Last year’s tax return if available&nbsp;</span></p></li></ol><p><br  /></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">适用人群：</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">International students, teachers, and researchers (F, J, M or Q status)*&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"p3\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">*The following will disqualify you from VITA: 1099-MISC, Capital Gains, Rental Income, Sale of Real Property, Gain for Sale of Personal Property, Dividends&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"p3\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br  /></span></p><p class=\"p3\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">重要提醒：</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">If the US ITIN on your 1042-S begins with a 999#, you will need to apply for an Individual Taxpayer ID. Make an appointment with Tracey McGoey (tmcgoey@lsu.edu) in LSU Accounting Services/Payroll before mailing your tax return.&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"p3\"><br  /></p><p class=\"p1\"><br  /></p><p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;text-decoration: underline;\">Additional Income Tax Resources&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;text-decoration: underline;\"> </span></p><p class=\"p1\"><br  /></p><p class=\"p2\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Internal Revenue Services (IRS):&nbsp;</span></strong></p><p class=\"p2\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">U.S. Federal tax forms and instructions are available on the IRS website at&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"p2\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">https://www.irs.gov/forms-instructions.&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"p2\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><br  /></span></p><p class=\"p2\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">For general tax information for international students and schol-ars, visit:&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"p2\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">www.irs.gov/individuals/international-taxpayers/ foreign-students-and-scholars&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"p2\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><br  /></span></p><p class=\"p2\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">If you are unable to attend the VITA meetings, the IRS offers a free Foreign Student Course where you can learn more about filing a U.S. Income Tax Return:&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"p2\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">https://apps.irs.gov/app/vita/ foreign_student.jsp?level=&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"p2\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><br  /></span></p><p class=\"p2\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Louisiana Department of Revenue:&nbsp;</span></strong></p><p class=\"p2\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Forms for filing state of Louisiana taxes can be found online at www.rev.state.la.us/Forms/ForIndividuals.&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"p2\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><br  /></span></p><p class=\"p2\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">LSU Accounting Services/Payroll:&nbsp;</span></strong></p><p class=\"p2\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Tax forms that you may need from LSU will be mailed in mid– to late February. You may be able to access your W-2 in Workday.&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"p2\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><br  /></span></p><p class=\"p2\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">You can find Tax Treaty information on Accounting Services website at www.lsu.edu/administration/ofa/oas/pay/ internationalemployees/tax.php. If you have questions about the tax forms or Tax Treaty information, you can contact Ms. Yolanda Clark (yvalle1@lsu.edu).&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"p2\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><br  /></span></p><p class=\"p2\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">International students on scholarship who are not eligible for a Social Security Number should apply for an Individual Taxpayer Identification Number (ITIN). For questions about the IITIN, con-tact Ms. Tracey McGoey (tmcgoey@lsu.edu).&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"p2\"><br  /></p><p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;background-color: rgb(212, 250, 0);\"><strong>祝大家都顺利退税～～</strong></span></p><p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;background-color: rgb(255, 172, 213);\"></span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"\" data-backh=\"400\" data-backw=\"558\" data-copyright=\"0\" data-ratio=\"0.7165492957746479\" data-src=\"https://mmbiz.qpic.cn/mmbiz_gif/cGcYqtanUys41PbKrYtVPia4vaKDicUhyOf0NHmPvwhSxf5RiaS1WazicZxABAY6aohB2p07uicPlfSjDb5WYVKa5ag/640?wx_fmt=gif\" data-type=\"gif\" data-w=\"568\" style=\"width: 100%;height: auto;\"  /></p><p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;background-color: rgb(255, 172, 213);\"></span></p>","url":"http://mp.weixin.qq.com/s?__biz=MzIwMjAwNDUxMg==&mid=502456959&idx=1&sn=5b5a5460ba7a57eb8ab3663b9ea0daba&chksm=0ee3033039948a26b0320898c42fb0d9a37e91ef36faf38f78c357dc98de1d103be2cae1f880#rd","thumb_media_id":"2EJIUVILHK642ZnYwwuOlozdXtnxgAyZjQheS4rPfY8","thumb_url":"http://mmbiz.qpic.cn/mmbiz_jpg/cGcYqtanUys41PbKrYtVPia4vaKDicUhyOgQp0gJvbSiaBP9n5Um2MxEib9fvLcM5XSZ2Ygr8cKrJAUg3hcyiaGJREg/0?wx_fmt=jpeg","u